The paper deals with the consensus problem in a distributed computing environment, which is a classic topic in distributed computing (cs.DC). The use of randomness and noise in the environment is a key aspect of the paper, which suggests that it could also be relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR).
